.TH "errseq_sample" 9 "errseq_sample" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
errseq_sample \- Grab current errseq_t value.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "errseq_t" errseq_sample
.BI "(errseq_t *eseq "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "eseq" 12
Pointer to errseq_t to be sampled.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function allows callers to initialise their errseq_t variable.
If the error has been "seen", new callers will not see an old error.
If there is an unseen error in \fIeseq\fP, the caller of this function will
see it the next time it checks for an error.
.SH "CONTEXT"
Any context.
.SH "RETURN"
The current errseq value.
